Mesothorax
: prescutum (prsc) rectangular to almost oval, probably rather convex, 96–106 μm long, 103–136 μm wide on mounted specimens; with small nodulations throughout; prescutal ridges (pscr) and prescutal suture (pscs) narrow; without prescutal setae. Scutum (sct) without a median membranous area; median area sclerotised but not reticulated; with 2 minute setae laterally on each side; lateral margins not reticulated, without setae. Prealare ridge quite well developed. Scutellum (scl) 124–148 μm wide, 41–56 μm long; possibly tubular, but with a large foramen; without scutellar setae (scls). Basisternum (stn 
2
) 188–230 μm wide, 73–83 μm long (rather spectacleshaped); with a strong median ridge (mdr) and bounded anteriorly by a strong marginal ridge (mr) and posteriorly by strong precoxal ridges (pcr 
2
); without basisternal setae (stn 
2
s); lateropleurite (lpl) quite broad anteriorly, without an extension from marginal ridge anteriorly; furca (f) well developed, unusual, without a waist, with short arms (each about 23 μm long), these parallel-sided but with tips diverging. Mesopostnotum (pn 
2
) well developed; postnotal apophysis (pna) apparently represented by an area of oval reticulations. Area bounded anteriorly by scutellum and laterally and posteriorly by mesopostnotum lightly sclerotised. Mesepisternum (eps 
2
) narrow, not reticulated; subepisternal ridge short; mesopleural apophysis (pla 
2
) long, extending internally. Postalare (pa) not reticulated anteriorly; without postalare setae (pas). Mesothoracic spiracle (sp 
2
) small: peritreme 18–21 μm wide, muscle plate broad and sclerotised. Postmesospiracular setae (pm 
2
s) absent. Tegula (teg) not detected; tegular setae (tegs) absent.

Metathorax
: metatergal setae (mts): absent. Dorsospiracular setae (dss) absent. Dorsal part of metapleural ridge (plr 
3
) present; suspensorial sclerite (ss) probably absent. Ventral part of metapleural ridge well developed; metepisternum (eps 
3
) probably unsclerotised, without postmetaspiracular setae (eps 
3
s) on either side. Metepimeron (epm 
3
) well developed but without setae. Membrane bounded anteriorly by scutellum and posteriorly by postnotum lightly striated. Antemetaspiracular setae (am 
3
s) absent. Metathoracic spiracle (sp 
3
): 16–21 μm wide. Metasternum (stn 
3
) apparently membranous; metasternal setae (amss + pmss) absent.
